Xpath:

//input[@id='username'] 
//input[@name='username']
 //input[@type='text']
  //input[@type='text' and @id='username'] 
  //input[@type='text' or  @id='username'] 
  //button[@type='submit' and @class='radius'] 
  //input[placeholder='Full Name*']

Chained xpath 
//form[@class='form reg-custom']
//div[@class='w-full custom__border']
//div[@class='w-full custom__border xls:mt-20 mt-10']//li[2]

Indexing Xpath
(//div[@class='w-full custom__border xls:mt-20 mt-10'])[2]

If you not have any attribute. Need to use contains method in xpath.
//a[contains(text(), 'Login')]
//li//a[contains(text(), 'Login')]

Find element using entire xpath
//a[text()=’Playwright Testing’]


Find the element using axes xpath: Sibling, not direct parent chind relation that time we are using.
//input[@placeholder='Full Name*']//following::input    
//input[@placeholder='Full Name*']//following::input[4]

Preceding like similar following xpath. But it is working bottom to top.
//input[@id='phone']//preceding::input
//input[@id='phone']//preceding::input[3]
//ul[@id='menu-side-menu']//li[@id='menu-item-1423']//preceding-sibling::li[2]


CSS Selector:

1.	find direct child name :
form.form.reg-custom > div:nth-child(2)
2.	Find Element like Parent >> Many child >> Many Sub child :
ul.nav.navbar-nav.navbar-right.navbar_right_blog > li:nth-child(1)
